Well, you certainly are, boss,
like a wet tongue sticks to dry ice.

65
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:58,958
<i>The paralysis has already
been diagnosed by Dr. Hamilton.</i>

66
00:04:59,032 --> 00:05:01,399
- It's A.L.S.
- Lou Gehrig's disease.

67
00:05:01,468 --> 00:05:04,131
It's a lovely diagnosis.
They make movies about it.

68
00:05:04,204 --> 00:05:07,106
No tests, no treatment—
It's a disease of exclusion.

69
00:05:07,174 --> 00:05:09,973
- Because Hamilton has
excluded everything else.
- I haven't.

70
00:05:15,282 --> 00:05:17,308
What else could it be?

71
00:05:17,384 --> 00:05:20,047
- Guillain-Barré,
which would be reversible.
- Excellent.

72
00:05:20,120 --> 00:05:24,251
No. The progression of the paralysis
would be symmetric. His wasn't.

73
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:26,953
- Transverse myelitis.
- Hamilton tested for it. Negative.

74
00:05:27,027 --> 00:05:29,326
And he was negative
for masses and A.V.M...

75
