Oh, an M.R.I. Come on. For pneumonia?

91
00:06:40,467 --> 00:06:42,834
Dr. House thinks we
should test for other— House?

92
00:06:42,903 --> 00:06:47,034
Yeah, I heard about him.
Obsessive son of a bitch? That's him.

93
00:06:49,309 --> 00:06:52,302
So who do you think is
right, Hamilton or House?

94
00:06:52,379 --> 00:06:54,678
Hey, they're both
excellent physicians.

95
00:06:54,748 --> 00:06:56,683
Come on.

96
00:06:56,750 --> 00:07:00,380
One of 'em says A.L.S.
The other one says not A.L.S.

97
00:07:00,453 --> 00:07:02,388
You gotta pick one, son.

98
00:07:02,455 --> 00:07:05,823
Everything points to A.L.S.

99
00:07:05,892 --> 00:07:08,418
Then no M.R.I.

100
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:15,451
And I want one of them
papers that say, uh, I

101
00:07:15,475 --> 00:07:17,601
don't want nothing
done if something go bad.

102
00:07:17,671 --> 00:07:21,506
A D.N.R.? Mr. Giles, you
don't want to rush into...

103
00:07:21,574 --> 00:07:25,067
It's been two years. I ain't
rushin'. I want to sign one.

104
00:07:26,913 --> 00:07:28,905
Now.

105
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:32,075
While my arm still works.

106
00:07:33,620 --> 00:07:36,021
♪♪

107
00:07:57,444 --> 00:07:59,208
