110
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:09,881
Oh. That makes more sense.

111
00:08:11,424 --> 00:08:13,916
- You tell him
it might not be A.L.S.?
- No.

112
00:08:15,295 --> 00:08:17,287
Well, no wonder he
signed. Who wouldn't?

113
00:08:17,364 --> 00:08:20,391
I started him on I.V.
steroids and Synthroid.

114
00:08:20,467 --> 00:08:25,132
Great. If it was <i>my</i> case, I'd be
adding a little I.V.I.G. to the mix.

115
00:08:25,205 --> 00:08:28,733
- For his pneumonia?
- That's my story, and I'm sticking to it.

116
00:08:30,343 --> 00:08:32,574
He doesn't want anything
done. No treatment.

117
00:08:33,646 --> 00:08:38,175
D.N.R. means "Do not
resuscitate," not "Do not treat."

118
00:08:38,251 --> 00:08:41,380
You do nothing, doesn't
matter which one of us is right.

119
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:46,126
And hang on to that D.N.R.

120
00:08:46,192 --> 00:08:48,593
That signature could be
worth a lot of money real soon.

121
00:08:48,661 --> 00:08:51,529
<i>♪♪</i>

122
00:08:55,869 --> 00:08:59,271
<i>This is Dr. Foreman.
What is Mr. Giles's status?</i>

123
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:02,776
Okay. Increase the steroids to 100
milligrams every 12 hours and, uh...

124
00:09:02,842 --> 00:09:06,006
start him on I.V.I.G.

125
00:09:06,079 --> 00:09:08,605
Yeah. Yeah, I'm sure.
One gram per kilo.

126
00:09:10,683 --> 00:09:12,709
<i>My nature isn't
what it used to be.</i>

127
00:09:12,786 --> 00:09:15,119
The little man has lost
some bounce in his step.

128
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:19,387
He needs to crank it up, have
himself some fun this weekend.

129
00:09:19,459 --> 00:09:23,829
He wants the blue pills. You're taking
about your penis in the third person.

130
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:26,128
Me and him—two people.

131
00:09:26,199 --> 00:09:29,328
Separate vacations? That'd
be a drag for one of you.

132
00:09:29,402 --> 00:09:33,464
<i>I don't think you need the pills. I
think you have a conflict in medications.</i>

133
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:38,240
- You need to up your insulin
to chocolate chip ice-cream levels.
- Insulin?

134
00:09:38,311 --> 00:09:40,974
Yeah. You remember. That's
the stuff you take for the diabetes...

135
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:43,482
<i>that you forgot to
tell the nurse about.</i>

136
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:46,213
Your hands...

137
00:09:46,286 --> 00:09:49,347
No hair, which
means nerve damage.

138
00:09:49,422 --> 00:09:51,492
And your shoes look
about two sizes too small,

139
00:09:51,516 --> 00:09:53,655
which means you've
lost sensation in your feet.

140
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:55,558
And then there's your pants.

141
00:09:55,628 --> 00:09:59,190
