No. They tell me you're an idiot.

142
00:09:59,265 --> 00:10:02,895
<i>Powdered sugar
on the right pant leg.</i>

143
00:10:02,969 --> 00:10:04,835
Based on the two
napkins in your pocket...

144
00:10:04,904 --> 00:10:07,601
<i>I'd bet it's not your first
doughnut of the day.</i>

145
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:19,712
You're giving me the
pills? Sure. Why not?

146
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:23,120
If you've got heart disease from
ignoring the diabetes, they'll kill you.

147
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:26,719
Otherwise, you two
have a fun weekend.

148
00:10:35,368 --> 00:10:37,303
O₂ sats are dropping.

149
00:10:37,370 --> 00:10:38,963
- Breath sounds?
- Junky.

150
00:10:39,038 --> 00:10:40,802
Mucus plug? <i>No,
it's our mistake.</i>

151
00:10:40,874 --> 00:10:43,241
<i>Sludging from the I. V. I. G.
Blood can't get to his lungs.</i>

152
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:46,609
Start heparin—500 c.c.'s I.V. push.
He won't last long enough for it to work.

153
00:10:46,679 --> 00:10:49,046
We've got to intubate him stat.

154
00:10:49,115 --> 00:10:51,482
We can't. He's D.N.R.

155
00:10:51,551 --> 00:10:53,486
What?

156
00:11:01,227 --> 00:11:03,696
Someone likes music. Oh, yeah.

157
00:11:09,736 --> 00:11:12,270
His sats are in the 70s.
How long's he been like this?

158
00:11:12,294 --> 00:11:12,934
Ten minutes.

159
00:11:13,006 --> 00:11:15,518
- Why aren't you— - The I.V.I.G.
put him in respiratory failure.

160
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:17,977
- You put him on I.V.I.G.?
- We did this.

161
00:11:18,044 --> 00:11:20,570
So undo it. Chase?

162
00:11:20,647 --> 00:11:23,344
- It's too late. We killed him.
- Nobody killed him. He's not dead.

163
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:26,181
- Chase, intubate him.
- He's D.N.R.

164
00:11:36,896 --> 00:11:38,865
What are you doin'?

165
00:11:43,836 --> 00:11:46,465
You can't do this!

166
00:11:47,607 --> 00:11:50,338
- Bag.
- You can't do this.

167
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:52,538
Bag!

168
00:12:00,019 --> 00:12:02,113
He had a bad reaction to
some medicine we gave him.

169
00:12:02,188 --> 00:12:05,022
What did you just do?

170
00:12:06,426 --> 00:12:08,054
He saved his life.

171
00:12:22,642 --> 00:12:25,134
<i>He's stable on the
ventilator, oxygenating well.</i>

172
00:12:25,211 --> 00:12:27,544
The I.V.I.G. made him worse,

173
00:12:27,614 --> 00:12:31,073
which means multifocal motor
neuropathy was a bad diagnosis.

174
00:12:31,150 --> 00:12:33,813
Okay, what's really wrong with
him? What's wrong with you?

175
00:12:33,886 --> 00:12:36,865
Everyone knows what's wrong with me.
What's wrong with <i>him</i> is more interesting.

176
00:12:36,889 --> 00:12:38,767
You tubed him, and
he didn't want to be

177
00:12:38,791 --> 00:12:40,985
tubed. He has a legal
paper saying just that.

178
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:44,224
To intubate or not to intubate—
That is the big ethical question.

179
00:12:44,297 --> 00:12:47,563
Actually, I was hoping we could avoid it
and maybe just practice some medicine.

180
00:12:47,634 --> 00:12:50,331
There is no question.
It's the patient's decision.

181
00:12:50,403 --> 00:12:52,338
If the patient is
competent to make it.

182
00:12:52,405 --> 00:12:56,035
