nothing to do with his A.L.S.
- Exactly! It's the I.V.I.G.

187
00:13:10,657 --> 00:13:14,890
You screwed up! You're not gonna
let him die because you screwed up.

188
00:13:16,129 --> 00:13:18,655
Technically, your
case. You screwed up.

189
00:13:18,731 --> 00:13:22,361
Is that what this is about— Looking
bad in front of your old boss?

190
00:13:22,435 --> 00:13:25,200
You assaulted that man.
Fine. I'll never do it again.

191
00:13:25,271 --> 00:13:27,631
Yes, you will. All the more
reason this debate is pointless.

192
00:13:33,346 --> 00:13:37,249
His lungs are
worse. Any theories?

193
00:13:37,317 --> 00:13:41,345
Oh, I'm sure he just went to the
little boys' room. Come on, people.

194
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:44,789
- Um, vasculitis?
- Wouldn't likely hit both lungs.

195
00:13:44,857 --> 00:13:47,588
It could be Wegener's
granulomatosis.

196
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:50,596
Dr. House?

197
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:53,531
Cuddy sent me a stripper again?

198
00:13:53,599 --> 00:13:55,795
Love that woman. So thoughtful.

199
00:13:55,868 --> 00:13:57,598
Sorry.

200
00:13:59,472 --> 00:14:02,772
There are case reports of Wegener's
hitting both the lungs and the spine.

201
00:14:02,842 --> 00:14:06,370
Well, it's not great, but it's better
than A.L.S. At least it's treatable.

202
00:14:06,446 --> 00:14:09,712
<i>It's a restraining order. You're not to
come within 50 feet of John Henry Giles,</i>

203
00:14:09,782 --> 00:14:12,581
and they've asked the D.A. to
file criminal charges for battery.

204
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:17,517
Cameron, test the
blood for C-ANCA.

205
00:14:17,590 --> 00:14:19,207
These are criminal
charges. They're not

206
00:14:19,231 --> 00:14:21,083
gonna let you take
blood to make more tests.

207
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:23,994
He has blood left in the
lab. Just add on the C-ANCA.

208
00:14:24,063 --> 00:14:27,795
- Foreman still got you doing bronchoscopic
suctioning for the pneumonia?
- Every four hours.

209
00:14:27,867 --> 00:14:30,254
Well, while you're
down in his lungs, grab a

210
00:14:30,278 --> 00:14:32,635
biopsy. We'll need it
to confirm Wegener's.

211
00:14:32,705 --> 00:14:35,402
- And move the patient
to the second floor I.C.U.
- Why?

212
00:14:35,475 --> 00:14:39,105
It's right above the clinic. I'm pretty
sure it's 50 feet in any direction.

213
00:14:40,179 --> 00:14:43,115
It's nice having a court order saying
you don't have to work clinic duty.

214
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,995
Dr. Cuddy! Excuse me.

215
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,332
You paged me. Why the yelling?

216
00:15:07,407 --> 00:15:11,071
His bed is behind that
wall— The plaintiff's.

217
00:15:11,144 --> 00:15:13,306
I can't, you know,
come any closer.

218
00:15:14,647 --> 00:15:17,276
It's right over the
clinic. Very cute.

219
00:15:17,350 --> 00:15:20,218
Can we get the lecture
over with 'cause I've gotta...

220
00:15:21,287 --> 00:15:23,688
Actually, I've got nothing
to do. Take your time.

221
00:15:23,756 --> 00:15:26,351
You need a lawyer?

222
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:28,918
You don't have a
problem with what I did?

